The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has extended the closing dates for the purchase and submission of Expression of Interest and Nomination Forms ahead of the 2023 general elections. According to a statement signed by PDPâ€™s National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba, this is to enable the Party to make up for the two days public holidays during Easter. The last day for the purchase of all forms was Thursday, April 14, 2022, while the last day for the submission of all forms was April 17, 2022. The initial dates for screening of aspirants for State House of Assembly: April 19, 2022, National Assembly: April 20, 2022, Governorship: April 21, 2022, and for Presidential: April 25, 2022. https://dailypost.ng/2022/04/07/2023-again-pdp-adjusts-timetable-extends-sales-of-nomination-forms/ However, the following dates have now been fixed for the screening of aspirants: State House of Assembly: Friday, April 22, 2022,
